HEADWORD: Stomodaeum
<hw>Stom`o*dae"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/, <?/, mouth + <?/ to divide.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A part of the alimentary canal. See under
<er>Mesenteron</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The primitive mouth and esophagus
of the embryo of annelids and arthropods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stomp</ent>⟦br⟧
